<h2>Project Goals</h2>
<p>
The true purpose behind this project is learning how to collect, organize, and visualize data. However, number systems are my crack. So, ultimately it's a chance for me to learn while pouring through numbers.
</p>
<p>
A toned-down explanation of the Martingale betting systems is that you bet a single amount on an even money bet. If you win, you collect the profit. If you lose, you continue doubling your bet until you win again. At that point, you will profit 1 original bet.
</p>
<p>
Mathematically, you can't lose in a system that is allowed to run forever. To counter this, casinos restrict max bets.
</p>
